data.text:
@Eva14043919 @Eva14043919

I can unfortunately look at bookings here on Twitter. Please contact our support by chat or phone with the booking reference so we can look at the booking and see what rules that applies to it.  https://t.co/b3QIqPk7bj

Regards,
Peter

@dinzramartell @dinzramartell

If all flights in a booking is operated by us, extra baggage can be added through our homepage or phone support. If any flight is operated by a partner,  the extra baggage need to be added at the airport.

Regards,
Peter

@dinzramartell Hi, when you purchase flights with SAS and other airlines, you will need to pay for the bags at the airport in order to ensure your bag goes the entire way, if it is a possibility. This also avoid being charged separately per airline for the added bag.
Kind regards, Rebecka
